The weights vector had a single item with value zero: I presume std::discrete_distribution is unwilling to return a distribution from that (and fair enough). I don't know enough about this to know if it's never supposed to get into that state, or if you can just check to see if weights has total weight zero and in that case just do a uniform distribution.

If needed I could start trying to narrow down a smaller test case, but that might take a while. Tried the same thing twice and got identical result.

